To save local system changes to git repository using terminal:
    git init                             [this will initialise empty git repo in current working directory]
    git status                           [this will return current branch details, any modified files that needs add and commit]
    git add modified_file_name           [this will save the changes]
    git commit -m "name_for_changes"     [this will commit changes]
    git config
        git config --global user.name "-----"
        git config --global user.email "-------"
        git config --list                [this will show git credentials]
    git branch -r                        [this will list available branches]
    git checkout desired_branch          [this will take to desired branch]
    git clone url                        [this will clone the content to the server]
